## Documentation Usage Patterns

### For New Contributors
1. Start with [README.md](mdc:README.md) for project overview
2. Review [Implementation Checklist](mdc:Docs/Development/Implementation-Checklist.md) for current status
3. Follow [Repository Setup](mdc:Docs/Development/Repository-Setup.md) for environment setup
4. Implement components following the detailed guides in `Docs/Development/`

### For Module Developers  
1. Read [Getting Started Guide](mdc:Docs/01-getting-started.md) for basic concepts
2. Study [Sample Modules Implementation](mdc:Docs/Development/Sample-Modules-Implementation.md) for patterns
3. Reference [API Reference](mdc:Docs/08-api-reference.md) for available APIs
4. Use [Troubleshooting](mdc:Docs/15-troubleshooting.md) for debugging

### For Framework Contributors
1. Review [Implementation Checklist](mdc:Docs/Development/Implementation-Checklist.md) for current priorities  
2. Follow the specific implementation guide for your component
3. Update the checklist when completing items
4. Add tests and documentation as outlined in each guide

### For Advanced Features
- **Hot-Reload**: [Hot-Reload](mdc:Docs/06-hot-reload.md) + [Hot-Reload Implementation](mdc:Docs/Development/Hot-Reload-Implementation.md)
- **Settings**: [Settings Schema](mdc:Docs/03-settings-schema.md) + [Settings Management Implementation](mdc:Docs/Development/Settings-Management-Implementation.md)  
